<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-xs-offset-0 col-sm-offset-1 col-sm-5">
      <h3>Create a Session</h3>
      <p>After a student record has been created, a user needs to create a session before collecting observations.  There
         are two ways in which a session can be created.
         <ol>
           <li>
             First, you can view the student record for the student whom you
              wish to observe.  Then, select the "Create Session" button below the student record (as indicated in the image)
           </li>
           <li>
             The second option is to go to the Student Record homepage where all student records are listed.  Then, two steps need to be completed
             <ol>
               <li>First, click on the "Create Sessions" button (Option 2 - Part A).</li>
               <li>After you complete this task, you will see a page
                 which offers two options.  The first is to create a student, which is required if there is no student record created for individual you will be observing.
                 However, if a student record already exists, you can click "Existing Student".  This display a list of all student records.  From here, simply click "Select Student" for the
                 row of the studen whom you will be observing (Option 2 - Part B).</li>
             </ol>
           </li>
         </ol>
       </p>

       <p>Regardless of the method used, a session must be associated with a student record.  For Option 1, the session will automatically be associated with the
         student record you were viewing.  For Option 2, you will be asked to select a student from a list.</p>
       <p>Once a session has been associated with a student, you will be prompted to complete a session form.</p>

       <p class="underline">Session Form</p>
       <p>The create session form is where a user lists details about a session and is able to customize how data is collected.  The session setting, session
         task, interval time, and number of intervals, are all required fields.  Note that the total observation time is calculated at the bottom of the form.
      </p>
